">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">q</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">q</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Prime.html#Ideal.IsPrime\">IsPrime</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"We say that an `R`-algebra `A` is unramified at a prime `q` of `A`\nif `A_q` is formally unramified over `R`.\n\nIf `A` is of finite type over `R` and `q` is lying over `p`, then this is equivalent to\n`κ(q)/κ(p)` being separable and `pA_q = qA_q`.\nSee `Algebra.isUnramifiedAt_iff_map_eq` in `RingTheory.Unramified.LocalRing` ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Unramified/Locus.html#Algebra.IsUnramifiedAt","kind":"def","line":39,"name":"Algebra.IsUnramifiedAt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Unramified/Locus.lean#L39-L46"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.RingTheory.Etale.Kaehler","Mathlib.RingTheory.LocalRing.ResidueField.Fiber","Mathlib.RingTheory.Support","Mathlib.RingTheory.Localization.InvSubmonoid"],"instances":[{"className":"Algebra.FormallyUnramified","name":"Algebra.instFormallyUnramifiedAtPrimeOfIsUnramifiedAt","typeNames":["Localization.AtPrime","Localization.AtPrime"]}],"name":"Mathlib.RingTheory.Unramified.Locus"}